 Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Checkenden, Oxfordshire, England":"Checkendon, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Marmion","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: perhaps an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name. Compare   Merriman  .","English (Lancashire; of Norman origin) and French: nickname from Old French <i>marmion</i> ‘monkey, brat’."],"variants":[{"name":"Merriman","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>mirie</i>, <i>merie</i>, <i>murie</i> ‘merry, pleasant’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   Merry   1. This surname is established in Ireland (perhaps as an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name; compare   Marmion  ) as well as England.","there has probably been some confusion with <b>Marriman</b>, probably an occupational name meaning ‘servant of <i>Mary</i>’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’, or perhaps a pet form of <i>Mary</i> using the hypocoristic suffix -<i>man</i>. The surname <i>Marriman</i> is now vanishingly rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Marmon","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Gloucestershire):","variant of   Marmion  .","variant of <b>Marriman</b>, an occupational name meaning ‘servant of Mary’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Marmion was born in 1260, in Checkendon, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Marmion, was 31 and his mother, Matilda Justice, was 30. He had at least 1 son with Margery de Nottingham. He died in 1331, in his hometown, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1260–1331":"1260–1331","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1263–130